## 7. What You Need To Run It Locally

### Prerequisites
- **Node.js 18+** (v20+ recommended)
- **MongoDB** — you need either:
  - A MongoDB Atlas cloud URI (the production one), or
  - A local MongoDB instance running on `mongodb://localhost:27017`
- **Git** (already have it)

### Environment Files

#### `server/.env` (CREATE THIS — not in git)
```env
MONGODB_URI=mongodb+srv://<user>:<password>@<cluster>.mongodb.net/<dbname>
JWT_SECRET=<any-random-string-at-least-32-chars>
SMTP_USER=<gmail-address>
PASSWORD=<gmail-app-password>
CLIENT_URL=http://localhost:5173
```

#### `client/.env.development` (ALREADY EXISTS)
```env
VITE_API_URL=
```
> Empty `VITE_API_URL` is correct for local dev — the Vite proxy handles routing to `localhost:3000`.

### Setup Steps

```powershell
# 1. Install server dependencies
cd c:\Users\Harma\OneDrive\Documents\GitRepos\_ViacoreMedia\SourceOneFinancial\server
npm install

# 2. Install client dependencies
cd ..\client
npm install

# 3. Create server/.env (see above)

# 4. Seed the admin account (first time only)
cd ..\server
node scripts/seedAdmin.js

# 5. Start the server (Terminal 1)
npm start
# → Server listening on port 3000

# 6. Start the client (Terminal 2)
cd ..\client
npm run dev
# → http://localhost:5173
```

### Login Credentials
The seed script creates a `super_admin` account. Check `scripts/seedAdmin.js` for the default email/password, or set them via env vars in the script.

### Production URLs
| Component | URL |
|-----------|-----|
| API | `https://source-one-data-transfer.vercel.app` |
| Frontend | Separate Vercel project (check Vercel dashboard for exact URL) |

